'''Federico Sebastián Viñas Barboza''' (born 30 June 1998) is a Uruguayan professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for {{Spanish football updater|Oviedo}} club [[Real Oviedo]], on loan from [[Liga MX]] club [[Club León|León]], and the [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay national team]].

==Club career==
===Juventud de Las Piedras===
After pursuing a pro career as a young boy, Viñas initially ceased his professional aspirations during his teenage years and began delivering meat to make a living. In 2017, he returned to the sport, beginning his career with [[Juventud de Las Piedras|Juventud]] in his native [[Uruguay]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://esto.com.mx/808222-federico-vinas-pasaria-de-repartir-carne-a-interesar-en-europa/|title=Federico Viñas pasó de retirarse y repartir carne a ser buscado por equipos europeos|trans-title=Federico Viñas went from retiring and handing out meat to being sought by European teams|language=Spanish|first=Juan Antonio|last=Davalos|work=esto.com.mx|date=3 April 2024|accessdate=8 July 2024}}</ref>

====Loan to Club America====
On 29 August 2019, Viñas joined Mexican side [[Club América]] on a one-year loan agreement with the option for a permanent deal.<ref>{{cite web|title=Federico Viñas, el nuevo ariete azulcrema|url=https://www.esto.com.mx/446588-federico-vinas-refuerzo-fichaje-aguilas-america-liga-mx-futbol-de-estufa-uruguay-ultimas-noticias-hoy-agosto-torneo-apertura-2019-agosto/ |website=esto.com.mx |publisher=Esto |language=Spanish |accessdate=29 August 2019}}</ref> He made his [[Liga MX]] debut on 14 September against [[Club Universidad Nacional|Universidad Nacional]]. He entered the match as a 77th minute substitute and scored 28 seconds later to break the scoreless deadlock.<ref>{{cite web|title=Debut goleador de Federico Viñas con América |url=https://www.tudn.mx/liga-mx/federico-vinas-debuta-con-gol-en-el-america |publisher=TUDN |language=Spanish |accessdate=14 September 2019}}</ref> Viñas appeared in eleven matches during the [[2019–20 Liga MX season #Torneo Apertura|Apertura]] tournament, managing to score five goals, three of which were scored in the [[Apertura 2019 Liga MX championship stage|championship stage]]; he scored one goal against [[Tigres UANL]] in the second leg of the quarterfinals, against [[Monarcas Morelia]] in the second leg of the semifinals, and once more in the second leg of the championship match against [[C.F. Monterrey|Monterrey]] at the [[Estadio Azteca]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/espanol/deportes/articulo/2019-09-26/el-uruguayo-federico-vinas-dice-estar-feliz-de-ser-el-talisman-del-america-mexicano |title=El uruguayo Federico Viñas dice estar feliz de ser el 'talismán' del América mexicano |language=Spanish |work=Los Angeles Times |accessdate=26 September 2019}}</ref>

===Club America===
On 30 May 2020, it was announced that America had exercised their $1.9&nbsp;million option to sign Viñas on a five-year contract, with the loan move becoming permanent on 1 July.<ref>{{cite web|title=Club América: ¿Cuánto costó el fichaje de Federico Viñas?|url=https://www.soyfutbol.com/ligas/Club-America-Cuanto-costo-el-fichaje-de-Federico-Vinas-20200530-0005.html|website=soyfutbol.com|publisher=SoyFutbol|language=Spanish|accessdate=30 May 2020}}</ref> After falling out of favor with the team during the [[2022–23 Liga MX season|2022–23]] season, making just four league starts over the course of the campaign, Viñas began attracting interest from clubs across the country.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.90min.com/es/posts/el-nuevo-equipo-que-tendria-federico-vinas-si-sale-del-america|title=El nuevo equipo que tendría Federico Viñas si sale del América|trans-title=The new team that Federico Viñas would have if he leaves América|language=Spanish|first=Uriel|last=Salmerón García|work=[[90min]]|date=15 December 2022|accessdate=8 July 2024}}</ref>

===León===
In June 2023, Viñas completed a $2 million move to [[Club León]], signing a four-year deal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.as.com/soccer/federico-vinas-signs-four-year-deal-with-leon-n/|title=Federico Viñas signs four-year deal with León|first=Guadalupe|last=Sena|work=en.as.com|date=24 June 2023|accessdate=8 July 2024}}</ref> He enjoyed a resurgent season with his new club, scoring 16 goals in 33 league appearances, becoming joint-top scorer in the [[2024 Clausura Tournament|2024 Clausura tournament]], and earning the league's Player of the Month award for November 2023.<ref name="POTM">{{cite web|url=https://www.soyfutbol.com/ligas/Club-Leon-Federico-Vinas-es-nombrado-jugador-del-mes-en-el-Apertura-2023-de-la-Liga-MX-20231209-0045.html|title=Club León: Federico Viñas es nombrado jugador del mes en el Apertura 2023 de la Liga MX|trans-title=Club León: Federico Viñas is named player of the month in Apertura 2023 of Liga MX|first=Josue|last=Garcia|work=Soy Futbol|date=9 December 2023|accessdate=8 July 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.as.com/soccer/federico-vinas-revelling-in-leon-rebirth-n/|title=Federico Viñas revelling in León rebirth|first=Aram|last=Ledezma|work=en.as.com|date=1 April 2024|accessdate=8 July 2024}}</ref>

In May 2024, Viñas ruptured his achilles while on international duty with Uruguay, which required surgery to repair.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://prosoccerwire.usatoday.com/2024/05/25/federico-vinas-injury-leon-star-torn-achilles-uruguay/|title=Leon star Viñas suffers torn Achilles with Uruguay ahead of Copa America|first=Seth|last=Vertelney|work=Pro Soccer Wire|date=25 May 2024|accessdate=8 July 2024}}</ref>

====Loan to Oviedo====
On 28 August 2024, Viñas joined Spanish [[Segunda División]] side [[Real Oviedo]] on a one-year loan deal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.realoviedo.es/noticias/federico-vinas-nuevo-futbolista-del-real-oviedo|title=Federico Viñas, nuevo futbolista del Real Oviedo|trans-title=Federico Viñas, new footballer of Real Oviedo|publisher=Real Oviedo|language=es|date=28 August 2024|accessdate=28 August 2024}}</ref>

==International career==
===Youth===
Viñas was included in [[Uruguay Olympic football team|Uruguay's U23]] squad for the [[2020 CONMEBOL Pre-Olympic Tournament]]. On 25 January 2020, Viñas scored his first goal with his national team in a 3–2 defeat against [[Bolivia national under-23 football team|Bolivia U23]].<ref>{{cite web |title=América's Federico Viñas scores magic diving header for Uruguay |url=https://en.onefootball.com/%F0%9F%8E%A5-americas-federico-vinas-scores-magic-diving-header-for-uruguay/ |website=onefootball.com |publisher=OneFootball |language=English |accessdate=25 January 2020 }}{{Dead link|date=August 2025 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>

===Senior===
Viñas played his first game for Uruguay in the CONMEBOL qualifiers coming in as a late substitute for [[Darwin Nuñez]], in their victory over Argentina on 16 November 2023. On 31 May 2026, he was named in Uruguay's 26-man squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Mundial 2026: Uruguay dio a conocer la lista de 26 convocados por Marcelo Bielsa|url=https://www.montevideo.com.uy/Deportes/Mundial-2026-Uruguay-dio-a-conocer-la-lista-de-26-convocados-por-Marcelo-Bielsa-uc963756|language=es|date=31 May 2026|access-date=31 May 2026}}</ref>

